      },
      {
        "from": "Image Worker",
        "to": "SQS Queue (message deletion)",
        "status": "risk",
        "issue": "Visibility timeout of 30s is dangerously close to worst-case batch processing time. A batch of 10 messages at ~3-4s each = 30-40s sequential processing. If any job in the batch takes longer than expected (network hiccup, large image), messages reappear in the queue and are processed a second time. Without idempotency guarantees, this causes duplicate processing, duplicate side effects, and wasted compute."
      }
    ],
    "contract_compliance": "SQS consumption contract is technically correct (MaxNumberOfMessages=10 is valid), but the consumer cannot honor the implicit SLA that jobs will be processed in a timely manner given the stated ingest rate.",
    "data_flow_integrity": "At risk. Without a dead-letter queue, poisoned messages (corrupt images, unsupported formats, oversized files) will cycle indefinitely between visible and invisible states, consuming worker capacity and compounding the throughput deficit. There is no mechanism to drain bad messages from the system."
  },

  "observability_review": {
    "logging": {
      "coverage": "gaps",
      "gaps": [
        "No logging of per-job processing duration — essential for diagnosing slow jobs and tuning batch sizes",
        "No logging of queue depth or approximate age of oldest message — operators cannot see backlog growth",
        "No logging of duplicate message detection (same MessageId processed twice due to visibility timeout expiry)",
        "No logging of batch receive size (did we get 0, 5, or 10 messages?) — critical for capacity planning"
      ]
    },
    "metrics": {
      "coverage": "Critically insufficient. Two counters (processed_total, failed_total) give success/failure rate but zero visibility into the actual operational health of the system.",
      "gaps": [
        "CRITICAL: No queue depth metric (ApproximateNumberOfMessagesVisible) — the single most important metric for this architecture. Without it, operators have zero visibility into the growing backlog.",
        "CRITICAL: No job processing duration histogram — cannot detect slow jobs, cannot set informed timeouts",
        "No queue age metric (ApproximateAgeOfOldestMessage) — cannot measure end-to-end latency from enqueue to completion",
        "No in-flight message count (ApproximateNumberOfMessagesNotVisible)",
        "No error categorization (transient vs permanent failure)",
        "No memory/CPU utilization of the worker process itself"
      ]
    },
    "tracing": {
      "coverage": "No distributed tracing mentioned. If the image processing is part of a larger pipeline (e.g., user uploads → API → SQS → worker → storage), there is no way to trace a single job across service boundaries.",
      "gaps": [
        "No correlation ID or trace ID propagation from upstream producer through to worker",
        "No span instrumentation for SQS receive → process → delete lifecycle"
      ]
    },
